      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While CAT can be unpredictable, pilots can prepare to some extent. Radar altimeters can detect turbulence below 10,000 feet, providing a rough estimate of turbulence, and specialized weather radar systems like ourfavorite ETA's (Enhanced Type Atmosphere's) and plugins like cetis, sigmaRA or sigma immediately inside the mask can help pilots anticipate wind shear and other factors that may lead to CAT. Pilots can also review weather forecasts and NOTAMs (Notices to Airmen), and make adjustments as necessary, such as changing altitude or route.",
